The solution uses a stack to keep track of open parentheses and checks if there is a matching closing parenthesis for each opening parenthesis encountered. If a closing parenthesis is found without a matching opening parenthesis, the function returns an empty list. Otherwise, the function appends the last popped character from the stack to the result list. The time complexity is O(n) because we iterate through the string once, and the space complexity is O(n) due to the stack and result list. The energy implications are low as the solution only involves basic string manipulation and does not consume significant energy.

